verses.text_plain: Rejoice not, O Israel, for joy, as other people: for thou hast gone a whoring from thy God, thou hast loved a reward upon every cornfloor.
verses.verse_html:
1Rejoice not, O Israel, for joy, as other people: for thou hast gone a whoring from thy God, thou hast loved a reward upon every cornfloor. ▼
▼ upon: or, in, etc

tokens.text: for thou hast gone a whoring

footnotes.body_html: ▼ upon: or, in, etc

verses.text_plain: The floor and the winepress shall not feed them, and the new wine shall fail in her.
verses.verse_html:
2The floor and the winepress shall not feed them, and the new wine shall fail in her. ▼
▼ winepress: or, winefat

verses.text_plain: They shall not dwell in the Lord’s land; but Ephraim shall return to Egypt, and they shall eat unclean things in Assyria.
verses.verse_html: 3They shall not dwell in the Lord’s land; but Ephraim shall return to Egypt, and they shall eat unclean things in Assyria.

verses.text_plain: They shall not offer wine offerings to the Lord, neither shall they be pleasing unto him: their sacrifices shall be unto them as the bread of mourners; all that eat thereof shall be polluted: for their bread for their soul shall not come into the house of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 4They shall not offer wine offerings to the Lord, neither shall they be pleasing unto him: their sacrifices shall be unto them as the bread of mourners; all that eat thereof shall be polluted: for their bread for their soul shall not come into the house of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: What will ye do in the solemn day, and in the day of the feast of the Lord?
verses.verse_html: 5What will ye do in the solemn day, and in the day of the feast of the Lord?

verses.text_plain: For, lo, they are gone because of destruction: Egypt shall gather them up, Memphis shall bury them: the pleasant places for their silver, nettles shall possess them: thorns shall be in their tabernacles.
verses.verse_html:
6For, lo, they are gone because of destruction: Egypt shall gather them up, Memphis shall bury them: the pleasant places for their silver, nettles shall possess them: thorns shall be in their tabernacles. ▼
▼ destruction: Heb. spoil
 , ▼
▼ the…: or, their silver shall be desired, the nettle, etc.: Heb. the desire

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the…: or, their silver shall be desired, the nettle, etc.: Heb. the desire
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the…: or, their silver shall be desired, the nettle, etc.: Heb. the desire

verses.text_plain: The days of visitation are come, the days of recompence are come; Israel shall know it: the prophet is a fool, the spiritual man is mad, for the multitude of thine iniquity, and the great hatred.
verses.verse_html:
7The days of visitation are come, the days of recompence are come; Israel shall know it: the prophet is a fool, the spiritual man is mad, for the multitude of thine iniquity, and the great hatred. ▼
▼ spiritual…: Heb. man of the spirit

footnotes.body_text: ▼ spiritual…: Heb. man of the spirit
footnotes.body_html: ▼ spiritual…: Heb. man of the spirit

verses.text_plain: The watchman of Ephraim was with my God: but the prophet is a snare of a fowler in all his ways, and hatred in the house of his God.
verses.verse_html:
8The watchman of Ephraim was with my God: but the prophet is a snare of a fowler in all his ways, and hatred in the house of his God. ▼
▼ in the: or, against the

footnotes.body_html: ▼ in the: or, against the

verses.text_plain: They have deeply corrupted themselves, as in the days of Gibeah: therefore he will remember their iniquity, he will visit their sins.
verses.verse_html: 9They have deeply corrupted themselves, as in the days of Gibeah: therefore he will remember their iniquity, he will visit their sins.

verses.text_plain: I found Israel like grapes in the wilderness; I saw your fathers as the firstripe in the fig tree at her first time: but they went to Baal–peor, and separated themselves unto that shame; and their abominations were according as they loved.
verses.verse_html: 10I found Israel like grapes in the wilderness; I saw your fathers as the firstripe in the fig tree at her first time: but they went to Baal–peor, and separated themselves unto that shame; and their abominations were according as they loved.

verses.text_plain: As for Ephraim, their glory shall fly away like a bird, from the birth, and from the womb, and from the conception.
verses.verse_html: 11As for Ephraim, their glory shall fly away like a bird, from the birth, and from the womb, and from the conception.

verses.text_plain: Though they bring up their children, yet will I bereave them, that there shall not be a man left: yea, woe also to them when I depart from them!
verses.verse_html: 12Though they bring up their children, yet will I bereave them, that there shall not be a man left: yea, woe also to them when I depart from them!

tokens.text: also to them when I depart

verses.text_plain: Ephraim, as I saw Tyrus, is planted in a pleasant place: but Ephraim shall bring forth his children to the murderer.
verses.verse_html: 13Ephraim, as I saw Tyrus, is planted in a pleasant place: but Ephraim shall bring forth his children to the murderer.

verses.text_plain: Give them, O Lord: what wilt thou give? give them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts.
verses.verse_html:
14Give them, O Lord: what wilt thou give? give them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts. ▼
▼ miscarrying: Heb. that casteth the fruit

footnotes.body_text: ▼ miscarrying: Heb. that casteth the fruit
footnotes.body_html: ▼ miscarrying: Heb. that casteth the fruit

verses.text_plain: All their wickedness is in Gilgal: for there I hated them: for the wickedness of their doings I will drive them out of mine house, I will love them no more: all their princes are revolters.
verses.verse_html: 15All their wickedness is in Gilgal: for there I hated them: for the wickedness of their doings I will drive them out of mine house, I will love them no more: all their princes are revolters.

verses.text_plain: Ephraim is smitten, their root is dried up, they shall bear no fruit: yea, though they bring forth, yet will I slay even the beloved fruit of their womb.
verses.verse_html:
16Ephraim is smitten, their root is dried up, they shall bear no fruit: yea, though they bring forth, yet will I slay even the beloved fruit of their womb. ▼
▼ the…: Heb. the desires

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the…: Heb. the desires

verses.text_plain: My God will cast them away, because they did not hearken unto him: and they shall be wanderers among the nations.
verses.verse_html: 17My God will cast them away, because they did not hearken unto him: and they shall be wanderers among the nations.

tokens.text: unto him: and they shall be wanderers
